Actress Tonto Dike has explained why she doesn’t attend burial ceremonies. The mother of one said she vowed since as a teenager not to attend burials and nothing will make her change her mind. King Tonto, as she’s fondly called, said that her mother’s burial might be the first ever she would attend. “I said this when I was a child and I will stick by it. My mom’s burial will/might be my first ever. “To all my friends that think I’m shutting them out, my reason is that I don’t attempt burials, if I let you attend my mom’s I will owe you same favour and I can’t repay that. “If you love me pray for my family, if you intend to support me, only pray for me. Don’t send a dime or a consolation message, I don’t do so well with that but know that I appreciate you all a lot and I am grateful.” (Thenation)     Actress Tonto Dikeh has, in an Instagram post, said that she and actor Uche Maduagwu are not friends, adding that they do not know each other. Uche, had in an Instagram post two days ago, referred to Tonto as his “friend” and “sister.”  He had said, “This woman [referring to… In "Entertainment" Mercy Johnson has castigated actor Uche Maduagwu for calling out Tonto Dike indirectly. She cautioned the actor to mind his words and avoid judging others. The mother of three said this following Uche’s advice to ladies to follow Mercy Johnson’s footsteps in marriage instead of Tonto Dikes ways which he… In "Entertainment" Nollywood actress, Tonto Dike, has revealed why she described her estranged husband, Olakunle Churchill as a “40 seconds” man. Tonto was responding to a fan who berated her for using Churchill’s alleged sexual deficiency to publicly shame him. Tonto said she made her ex-husband’s inabilities public because he first accused… In "Entertainment"